      "writtenOn": "2026-04-20T22:31:12Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Done in PS4. The code now uses ssl::host_name_verification via set_verify_callback. Commit msg notes that libcurl reaches the same check via 509_VERIFY_PARAM_set1_host — SSL_set1_host is a thin alias, and host_name_verification ends up calling X509_check_host under the hood. Three names, one check; libcurl is not skipping hostname verification.",
